Post-estimation treatment effects for an ETWFE regressions.

Source: R/emfx.R
emfx.Rd

Post-estimation treatment effects for an ETWFE regressions.

Usage

emfx(
  object,
  type = c("simple", "group", "calendar", "event"),
  summary = TRUE,
  ...
)

Arguments

object

An `etwfe` model object.

type

Character. The desired type of post-estimation aggregation.

summary

Logical. Should the resulting marginaleffects objects be passed to [`summary`] before being returned? Defaults to TRUE, but mostly for aesthetics reasons.

...

Additional arguments passed to [`marginaleffects::marginaleffects`].

Value

A marginaleffects object.

See also

[marginaleffects::marginaleffects()]

Examples

# We’ll use the mpdta dataset from the did package (which you’ll need to 
# install separately).

# install.packages("did")
data("mpdta", package = "did")

# Run the estimation
mod = etwfe(
    fml  = lemp ~ lpop, # outcome ~ controls
    tvar = year,        # time variable
    gvar = first.treat, # group variable
    data = mpdta,       # dataset
    vcov = ~countyreal  # vcov adjustment (here: clustered)
    )
mod
